OL,3,CUK fathers call for action over 'worst
OL,4,Cpaternity leave policy in Europe'
OL,6,FIntroduced in 2003, statutory
OL,7,Fpaternity leave allows most new
OL,8,Ffathers and second parents in the UK
OL,9,Fto take up to two weeks off work.
OL,11,FUK paternity leave pay is #187.18 a
OL,12,Fweek or 90% of their earnings,
OL,13,Fwhichever is lower.
OL,15,FThat means that eligible UK fathers
OL,16,Fand non-birthing parents currently get
OL,17,Ftwo weeks on less than half the
OL,18,Fminimum wage, with self-employed co-
OL,19,Fparents not qualifying for state
OL,20,Fsupport.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/14
